<h1>Script: author-element</h1>
<p>
  An author is used to define an author. <em>author</em> is an optional 
  attribute in a module. The definition-element may contain any number of author-elements.
 </p>
<pre class="mlcode">
  &lt;author id="" name=""&gt;...&lt;/author&gt;
</pre>

<table cellpadding="10px">
  <tr>
    <td valign="top"><strong>id</strong>(mandatory)</td>
    <td>Any string that will identify this author.
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign="top"><strong>name</strong>(mandatory)</td>
    <td>The displayed name of the author.
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<p>
 All modules are given a default author. You may 
 set this by the id: <em>_default</em>:
</p>
<pre class="mlcode">
  &lt;author id="_default" name="My self"/&gt;
</pre>
<p>
 If default author is not set it defaults to: "Site author".
</p>


<p>Examples:</p>

<pre class="prettyprint lang-html">
  &lt;author id="bs" name="Børre Stenseth"/&gt;
</pre>
<p>or</p>
<pre class="prettyprint lang-html">
  &lt;author id="bs" name="Børre Stenseth"&gt;
        &lt;![CDATA[
    &lt;div style="font-weight:bold"&gt;
        &lt;a href="http://www.a.b/mypage.html"&gt;homepage&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
     ]]&gt;
&lt;/author&gt;
</pre>



